data.title: When u roll a Nat 20 to dodge the snow golem's attack

images.description:
FP edit: omg my first print page post.
Ummm. Send funny dungeons and dragons stories.

This was my PR squat at 195 kg (429 lb).  Very happy with it overall.  There was a bit of hip shift to my left at the bottom of the squat but working near your max weight will really highlight those kinds of idiosyncrasies.

Big PR on the bench at 142.5 kg (314 lb).  This came as a total surprise as I was expecting to hit just over 300.  My first 2 attempts flew up easily so my coach increased my last attempt without telling me and I’m glad he did.

Kind of anticlimactic after the first 2 lifts.  I deadlifted a conservative 192.5 kg (424 lb). That was planned due to an injury and some setbacks in training.  Definitely had more in me, but no pain is also good.  Deadlifting has been my nemesis for the last couple of years and progress has been slow.  I’m planning on competing in a strongman show this summer and will need a strong conventional deadlift, so I’m looking forward to getting back to training.  The meet was hosted by Northside Athletics in Fairbanks, Alaska.  Best gym community I have ever been a part of.          FP Edit: Sweet! Never made the front page before! For those asking, I weighed in at 91.5 kg with my weight class being 93 kg.  These aren’t super competitive numbers but the nice thing about powerlifting is that unless you’re at the elite levels, you’re mostly competing against yourself.  I highly recommend anyone interested to give it a try regardless of how strong or weak you think you are.  My parting fitness advice is to find something you really enjoy doing: lifting, biking, hiking... competitive hopscotch.. and do it as much as you can.

images.description:
It's my birthday next month, and seeing as how I have no friends I thought I'd go someplace different. Hence Vienna.

It was only after booking the flights that I realised I know nothing about Vienna or Austria beyond the Sound of Music. Also Mozart died there, apparently. I was thinking of just packing a decent pair of walking shoes and loading up Pokemon Go for a few days and letting that decide, but when you say that out loud, it sounds incredibly stupid.
